replies.bodyText:
Just checked this. It seems simple literals are in their original type, so it doesn't count as a JSON tag. For example, the following works as expected:
import ballerina/io;

public function main() {
    json j1 = 10;
    io:println(j1.name);
}
j1 is a Long when you check at this point.

